<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: =
after-white-space;"><div>Kia ora Privacy =
Team,</div><div><br></div><div>Thanks for checking in. I can access the =
link; however, it is not identity-restricted. As a test, I could open =
the folder using a different, unknown email address simply by entering a =
name and passing reCAPTCHA. I=E2=80=99ve saved screenshots. Please treat =
this as a security issue.</div><div><br></div><div>For clarity, on 1 =
July 2025 I requested a full copy of my file for both claims (C90306048 =
and C90306256), =E2=80=9Cincluding all internal notes, reports, =
third-party correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, and any other =
material Tower holds in relation to these claims.=E2=80=9D</div><div>Legal=
 effect: Under IPP6 and s 44 Privacy Act 2020, I=E2=80=99m entitled to =
access my personal information. =E2=80=9CIncluding=E2=80=9D is =
non-exhaustive, covering all formats and systems (e.g., email, =
IM/Teams/Slack, call recordings/transcripts, SMS, photos/video, test =
results, and native costing spreadsheets). It also extends to =
information held for Tower by its agents/contractors (see s 11). If =
anything is withheld or redacted, please identify the specific ground(s) =
in ss 49=E2=80=9353, and release the balance as a severed copy (s =
46(2)(a)).</div><div><br></div><div>Fair Insurance Code: As a signatory, =
Tower commits to handling claims and complaints honestly, fairly, =
transparently, and in a timely way, with clear communication about what =
you will do and when. The insecure link, incomplete response, and broad =
redactions to date don=E2=80=99t feel consistent with those =
commitments.</div><div><br></div><div>I also want to note the human =
impact. I=E2=80=99m already dealing with the aftermath of the fire; the =
insecure link, incomplete response, and redactions have added avoidable =
stress and time burden.</div><div><br></div><div>REQUESTS AND =
TIMEFRAMES</div><div><br></div><div>A) Security / containment =E2=80=93 =
by 5:00pm NZT, Thursday 25 September 2025</div><div><br></div><div><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Revoke/disable the current link(s) and =
re-issue recipient-specific access tied solely to my email (no public =
link).</li><li>Provide ShareFile audit logs (link creation, permissions, =
and all access events: timestamp, user/email, IP, =
action).</li><li>Confirm the containment steps taken and whether a =
notifiable privacy breach assessment was made; if notified, please =
provide the OPC reference number; if not, please provide your =
serious-harm assessment.</li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>B) =
Substantive Privacy Act response =E2=80=93 by 5:00pm NZT, Thursday 25 =
September 2025</div><div>Please conduct a fresh, enterprise-wide search =
and provide the complete files across all systems and agents/contractors =
for both claims, including (non-exhaustive):</div><div><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Claim diary/notes and task logs (full =
chronology).</li><li>Internal communications: emails and IM (e.g., =
Teams/Slack).</li><li>Call recordings/transcripts for all calls with me =
(inbound/outbound), any video calls, and voicemail.</li><li>SMS/texts =
and chat messages with me.</li><li>Instructions to/from assessors and =
contractors, all quotes/scopes/variations, and native costing =
files/spreadsheets used to build any scope/SOW.</li><li>Site media: all =
photos and videos.</li><li>Testing/technical reports: moisture logs; =
soot/smoke/odour assessments; HVAC/duct contamination; asbestos =
sampling/clearances; electrical, gas, and engineering =
reports/results.</li><li>Third-party correspondence relating to my =
claims.</li><li>ShareFile configuration and access/audit logs for links =
used to provide my data.</li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>Please also =
provide a document index (date, author, short description, and =
system/location) so I can verify completeness. For each =
redaction/withholding, identify the specific ground(s).</div><div>To =
assist completeness, please include a brief search methodology (systems =
searched, date ranges, search terms, and which third parties were asked =
to supply records). If any category does not exist, please state that =
expressly.</div><div><br></div><div>C) Records preservation (effective =
immediately)</div><div>Please preserve all records relating to my claims =
=E2=80=94 until both claims have been fully settled and all requested =
documentation has been provided. This includes contractor files, access =
logs and backups. Kindly confirm &nbsp;that any automatic deletion =
settings have been paused for the relevant =
mailboxes/systems.</div><div><br></div><div>For reference, the current =
folder contains only six documents, which is plainly incomplete for a =
full file response. I=E2=80=99m keen to resolve this directly and will =
review whatever you provide promptly.</div><div><br></div><div>Ng=C4=81 =
mihi,</div><div>Raffaella del Prete</div><div><br></div><div =
class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" style=3D"direction: ltr;"><blockquote =
type=3D"cite"><div>On 18 Sep 2025, at 3:29=E2=80=AFPM, Privacy =
